            },
            {
                "Value": "Applicant with two or more losses or any single loss in excess of $7,500 within the prior five years",
                "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                "DisplayOrder": 0
            },
            {
                "Value": "<p><strong>Blanket waiver of subrogation</strong> may be added to policies with a blanket additional insured endorsement for an additional 5% of the GL&nbsp;premium, subject to $250. Use MEGL 0241-01.</p>\r\n",
                "GuidelineType": "Options",
                "DisplayOrder": 0
            },
            {
                "Value": "<p><strong>Waiver of subrogation</strong> may be added for additional insureds for an additional $100 each. Use MEGL 0241.</p>\r\n",
                "GuidelineType": "Options",
                "DisplayOrder": 0
            },
            {
                "Value": "<p><strong>Primary and noncontributory</strong> wording may be added for an additional $100 when used with individual additional insureds or $250 when used with blanket additional insureds. Use <strong>CG 20 01</strong>.</p>\r\n",
                "GuidelineType": "Options",
                "DisplayOrder": 0
            },
            {
                "Value": "<p>Individual additional insureds may be added for $100 each (use <strong>MEGL 0009, Additional Insured Endorsement</strong>). This is available for landlords, banks and lending institutions, municipalities, cities, counties, customers, general contractors, and project owners. If used for lending institutions/banks, there is no charge.</p>\r\n",
                "GuidelineType": "Options",
                "DisplayOrder": 0
            },
            {
                "Value": "<p>Blanket additional insured may be added for 10% of the GL premium, subject to $500 minimum (use <strong>MEGL 0009-01 Blanket Additional Insured</strong>). This form is available for any person or organization to whom you are obligated by valid written contract to provide such coverage.</p>\r\n",
                "GuidelineType": "Options",
                "DisplayOrder": 0
            }
        ],
        "GlRiskUnits": [
            {
                "CustomDescription": "Contractors - executive supervisors or executive superintendents",
                "GlClassification": {
                    "LineMinimumPremiumRequirement": 2500,
                    "Value": "91580-00",
                    "ValueType": "Id",
                    "Code": "91580",
                    "SubCode": "00",
                    "Description": "Contractors - executive supervisors or executive superintendents",
                    "ClassNotes": "<p><strong>Contemplated Operations</strong>: This classification is to be used for general contractors who supervise building projects and hire and pay all subcontractors. Work can be performed by direct employees or by subcontractors - we have no minimum or maximum acceptable percentage of subcontracted work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Construction Manager Exposures: We are not a market</strong> for construction manager exposures. A construction manager is an individual or firm authorized by the project owner to be responsible for coordinating time, equipment, money, tasks and people for a specific project. &nbsp;They will act as the eyes and ears for the project owner when it comes to project management/coordination duties and will have no contractual relationship with the primary contractor or any subcontractors. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Artisans</strong>: Trade or artisan contractors focusing on a single trade or a few related trades should be classified and rated under the appropriate artisan contractor class code(s). For example: a roofing contractor that subs out any percentage of their work&nbsp; should classified be rated under the appropriate roofing class code(s).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Remodeler Program</strong>: We have a remodeler product available ($1,000 MP for $1m/$2m limits) for eligible risks in this class code. Eligible risks will be contractors dedicated to the home remodeling space including whole bathroom and kitchen remodels, finish out work in bonus rooms, converting garages to living areas, room additions, etc. &nbsp; Average job values typically vary from $10,000 - $30,000 depending on the venue and size of a particular job. Incidental commercial work (up to 25%) is acceptable.&nbsp; Additional forms are attached automatically:&nbsp; MEGL 0300, Exclusion- New Residential Work Exclusion, MEGL 1349, Exclusion-Common Interest Dwelling Or Residence Conversions, &amp; MEGL 1614, Exclusion- Conditional Open Roofs and Specified Roofing Operations will apply.&nbsp; <strong>The remodeling program is not intended for handymen or contractors specializing in exterior home improvements (i.e. siding work, foundation work, roofing work, etc.)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The remodeling program is not currently available in the following states: AK, MT, NM, WA, or WY.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Handypersons (not intended for the regular GC or remodeling program)</strong>: will have lower average job values ($500 to $2,000) and are hired to do a variety of miscellaneous work for others, involving minor repairs in a household environment (i.e. patching a roof, hauling debris, minor painting, small plumbing repairs, etc.). Handypersons need to be classified and rated using class code <strong>95625 &ndash; Handyperson. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n"
                },
