                "Guidelines": [
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Subcontractors must be insured, name our applicant as additional insured and carry equal or greater limits. This warranty may be removed by removing MEGL 0103, Limitation &ndash; Contractor or Subcontractor Management form for a surcharge. The surcharge will vary from 5% to 30% depending on the amount of work the applicant subcontracts.&nbsp; Higher amounts of subcontracted work will result in higher surcharges. Likewise, higher payroll amounts (relative to subcontractor costs) will result in lower surcharges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>If subcontractors are used, add <strong>91583</strong> (residential) and/or <strong>91585</strong> (commercial) as &quot;Included&quot;. &nbsp;No additional rating, premium or forms apply.&nbsp;Please note: Quick Quote automatically adds these classes for you.&nbsp; You do not need to select the subcontracting codes when quoting on our system. &nbsp;</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>If the applicant does <strong>100% commercial work</strong>, you may credit the rate up to 25%, add the MEGL 1627, Exclusion - Residential Property Construction and delete the MEGL 1628, New Residential Construction Limitation.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>The number of homes or units worked on in a single project or development may not exceed 20 for applicants engaged in new residential construction except in the states of AZ, CA, CO, HI, ID, NV, OR, or UT where the number of homes or units worked on in a single project or development may not exceed 12.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
