                "CrimeSusceptibilityGrade": "Low",
                "Index": 7,
                "Eligibility": "Agent Authority",
                "Guidelines": [
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Subcontractors must be insured, name our applicant as additional insured and carry equal or greater limits. This warranty may be removed by removing MEGL 0103, Limitation &ndash; Contractor or Subcontractor Management form for a surcharge. The surcharge will vary from 5% to 30% depending on the amount of work the applicant subcontracts.&nbsp; Higher amounts of subcontracted work will result in higher surcharges. Likewise, higher payroll amounts (relative to subcontractor costs) will result in lower surcharges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>If subcontractors are used, add <strong>91583</strong> (residential) and/or <strong>91585</strong> (commercial) as &quot;Included&quot;. &nbsp;No additional rating, premium or forms apply.&nbsp;Please note: Quick Quote automatically adds these classes for you.&nbsp; You do not need to select the subcontracting codes when quoting on our system. &nbsp;</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>If the applicant does <strong>100% commercial work</strong>, you may credit the rate up to 25%, add the MEGL 1627, Exclusion - Residential Property Construction and delete the MEGL 1628, New Residential Construction Limitation.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>The number of homes or units worked on in a single project or development may not exceed 20 for applicants engaged in new residential construction except in the states of AZ, CA, CO, HI, ID, NV, OR, or UT where the number of homes or units worked on in a single project or development may not exceed 12.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "General",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Structural demolition",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Applicant performs work outside of their state of domicile",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Modular or manufactured housing construction or installation",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Project height exceeds three stories",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Propane, LPG or natural gas work",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Waterproofing",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Stucco work",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Street, road, bridge, or highway work including any right of way maintenance</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Off-premises welding",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "Fire or water restoration",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>House/building raising, lifting or moving</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Submit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Construction Manager exposures.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Prohibit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Handyperson risks.&nbsp; Handypersons need to be classified and rated using class code 95625 &ndash; Handyperson.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Prohibit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Application of mulch, fertilizer, compost, or similar material for others in the business of producing/growing crops, plants, etc. for commercial purposes.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Prohibit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Clearing, pruning, cutting, or removal of brush, trees, or other vegetation on or around power &amp; utility lines in the state of California.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Prohibit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>prescribed or controlled burn operations</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Prohibit",
                        "DisplayOrder": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Blanket additional insured may be added for 10% of the GL premium, subject to $500 minimum (use <strong>CG 20 33 Additional Insured - Owners, Lessees, or Contractors - Scheduled Person or Organization</strong>). This is the blanket version of the CG 20 10.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Individual additional insureds requiring the <strong>CG 20 10 Additional Insured - Owners, Lessees, or Contractors - Scheduled Person or Organization</strong> may be added for $100 each. Coverage provided by this endorsement is restricted to &quot;&quot;ongoing operations&quot;&quot;.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p>Individual additional insureds requiring the<strong> CG 20 37 Additional Insured-Owners, Lessees, or Contractors-Completed Operations</strong> may be added for $250 each.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 0
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p><strong>You may remove the MEGL 0103, Limitation &ndash; Contractor or Subcontractor Management</strong> warranty requiring all subcontractors to be insured<strong>,</strong> name the applicant as an additional insured and carry equal or greater limits for a rating surcharge. The surcharge for removal of the subcontractor warranty will range from 5% to 30% depending on level of payroll and subcontractors the applicant uses. The surcharge will be lower for applicants with higher payrolls; likewise, the surcharge will be higher for those applicants with more subcontractor costs.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p><strong>You may remove the CG 22 94, Exclusion- Damage to Work Performed by Subcontractors On Your Behalf</strong> on all our contracting class codes for a rating surcharge. The surcharge will range from 10%-55% depending on the amount of work that is subcontracted and the amount of new residential construction the applicant performs.&nbsp; Applicants with lower subcontractors costs and a lower amount of new residential work will receive lower surcharges. Likewise, applicants with heavier subcontractor costs and more new residential work will receive higher surcharges.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p><strong>Rating credits may be available </strong>on many of our contracting risks by providing payroll &amp; subcontractor cost information. The credits will range from -20% to -50% depending on the amount work subcontracted vs. that done with payroll.&nbsp; Applicants with heavy subcontractor costs and lower payroll amounts will receive higher credits compared to those accounts with heavier payroll amounts and lower subcontractor costs.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p><strong>The Contractors Bundle</strong> is available at no charge for eligible general contracting risks. The bundle consists of MEGL 0009-01, Blanket Additional Insured; MEGL 0241-01, Blanket Waiver of Subrogation; MEGL 0313, Per Project Aggregate; &amp; CG 20 01, Blanket Primary and Noncontributory-Other Insurance Condition.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "Value": "<p><strong>Contractor&#39;s Job Site Pollution</strong> coverage may be added when all chosen class codes on a risk are eligible for the coverage. We have three limit offerings available: A $1m/$1m limit may be added for 5% of the GL premium subject to a $350 minimum.&nbsp; A $500k/$500k limit may be added for 3.75% of the GL premium subject to a $250 minimum.&nbsp; A $250k/$250k limit may be added for 3% of the GL premium subject to a $150 minimum. Use form MEGL 1284, Contractor&rsquo;s Job Site Pollution Coverage.</p>\r\n",
                        "GuidelineType": "Options",
                        "DisplayOrder": 1
                    }
                ],
